text: Big Branch is an unincorporated community in St. Tammany Parish, Louisiana, United States. The community is located on U. S. Route 190 southeast of Mandeville and 3.5 miles northwest of Lacombe. The Big Branch Marsh National Wildlife Refuge lies along the coast of Lake Pontchartrain south of the community between Mandeville and Slidell.Louisiana Atlas & Gazetteer, DeLorme, 3rd ed., 2010, p. 48 Entrance sign to the big branch marsh national wildlife refuge. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in St. Tammany Parish, Louisiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Louisiana Category:Unincorporated communities in New Orleans metropolitan area
